          "text": "Here's a summary of `notes/subagents.md`:\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes a **sub-agent delegation system** where agents can spawn child agents to handle delegated tasks. Here are the key design decisions:\n\n### Core Model\n- Agents form a **tree** via `parent_id` (nil = root, parent's ID = child)\n- A `clone_agent` tool lets a running agent spawn a child with a copy of current context + new instruction\n- Parent's chat task **blocks** until the child completes a full turn\n\n### Architecture Highlights\n- **Context Inheritance**: Child gets parent's full message history plus the instruction\n- **Blocking Model**: Same pattern as compaction — chat task blocks on `receive`, child GenServer sends `{:child_completed, ...}` when idle\n- **Recursion**: Children can call `clone_agent` themselves; configurable max depth (default 3)\n- **Cascade Termination**: Killing a parent kills all children/grandchildren\n\n### Token Tracking — Three Concepts\n1. **Context Tokens** — per-call, what's sent to the LLM next\n2. **Direct Usage** — this agent's own LLM calls (existing `usage_totals`)\n3. **Total Usage** — direct + all descendants' total usage recursively (propagated upward at completion)\n\n### Agent State Changes\n- New fields: `parent_id`, `depth`, `pending_children`, `descendant_usage`\n\n### UI Changes\n- Flat agent list → **tree view**\n- \"Delegated Task\" card in parent's conversation (instruction, child ID link, status, response)\n- \"Back to parent\" link in child's conversation\n\n### All Open Questions Resolved\nAll 6 open questions at the bottom have been answered inline (max depth in DotConfig, cascade termination is clean, stopping parent stops child, children inherit tools minus `clone_agent` at max depth, etc.).\n\nWould you like me to do anything with this — review it, plan an implementation, or something else?",
